review_blob: Deep amber pour. Great head retention. Caramel & hops on the nose. Toffee, caramel & well balanced hops on the tongue. Great hop bitterness.
Dark amber pour. Small white head. Pine & resin on the nose. Explodes with hoppy pine resin on the tongue backed up nicely by the malt.
Golden Amber Pour. Small white head. Pungent piney nose, hints of citrus. Earthy hops & pine on the tongue. Full flavoured APA. Stunning beer.
Pale gold pour. Quickly fading white head. Sweet malt & grain aroma. Taste follows the nose. Low bitterness. Nothing special here.
Sweet hoppy, biscuity nose. Sprucey pine hop profile is complimented well by the biscuity malt. Warm finish with a lingering bitterness.
Good amber ale. Very subtle on the nose and then surprisingly complex on the palate. Toasty, Malty with toffee and caramel. Med dry finish.
Hazy amber pour, thick off white head. Sweet citrus hoppy nose. Medium bodied, bitter pine and resin on the tongue. Long dry bitter finish. Very good.
Blacker than black pour with thick brown head. Strong alcohol aroma. Oak, raisin and whiskey on the tongue with a velvety mouthfeel.
A bit dissapointing considering the promise of three hop and three malt varietals... I found it quite bland. I wouldnt bother to be honest.
Hazy gold pour Plenty flakes/floaters Clove, Banana, citrus aroma Fruity esters Belgian yeast taste dominates in a good way. Amazing beer!
Light gold pour. Quickly fading white head. Bready aroma. Typical lager with subtle taste of corn. Crisp, dry finish. Not the best by far.
Stunning beer. Amber pour. Thick frothy off white head.Yeasty fruity aroma. Bananas, apricots and other well balanced fruit on the tongue. Medium bitterness, tart, hoppy Finnish. Amazing beer.
Hazy orange pour. Yeasty, fruity, banana aroma. Apricot, banana and clove on the tongue. Moderate/low bitterness. Thoroughly enjoyable
Pale gold pour. Thickish white head. Tart and yeasty on the tongue with lively carbonation.
Dark gold pour with thick white fluffy head. Yeasty, honey, sweet aroma. Medium bitter honey on the tongue. Good use of hops. Sweet finish.
Beautiful amber pour,lively carbonation, small white head. Aroma is of caramel, malt and a hint of hops. Low bitterness. Metallic aftertaste.
Dark brown pour. Small dirty white head. Bready, biscuit aroma. Good roasted malt taste, suttle coffee notes. Medium bodied.

Dark pour. Thick, beige, frothy head. Rich fruit and nuts on the nose. Lively carbonation. More rich, dark fruits and candy sugar on the tongue. 
Complex and delicious.
Not as complex as a other IPAs. No real aroma, slight citrus notes with a fresh grassy taste. Very easy drinking IPA
Amber pour, small white head. Aroma is piney and a tad grassy. Great bitterness with good floral and citrus notes. Nice IPA.
Dark Gold Pour, white head, leaves delicate lacing. Citrus on the nose. Great fruity hop notes on the tongue. Complex, neat little pale ale.
beer_name: Matilda Bay Fat Yak Pale Ale

review_blob: Light gold pour, slight hop aroma. Sweet and malty on the tongue with slight bitterness. Smooth finish. Easy drinking safe beer.
Light gold pour with lively carbonation. Floraly, yeasty aroma. Light and fruity on the tongue, medium bitternes. Crisp, dry, clean finish.
Golden pour, quickly disappearing head. No real wow factor. Very subtle fruity hop aroma and taste. Feels like theres something missing.
beer_name: James Squire The Chancer Golden Ale

review_blob: Pale orange pour, slight head. Good carbonation. Yeasty banana aroma. Banana clove and vanilla on the tongue. Crisp, fresh mouthfeel
Dark amber pour small of white head. Slight hop & spice aroma. Light malt fruity flavour and a dash of hops. Slightly bitter finish.
Light gold pour. Small white head. Faint, grassy, hoppy nose. Clean light malt and grassy on the tongue. Moderate bitterness.

Deep orange pour. Good head leaves fragmented lacing. Grapefruit and Granadilla nose. Caramel malt on the tongue with a dash of citrus.
Good balance between hops and malt.
Cloudy yellow pour. Tiny head, no lacing. Aroma is yeasty, bready and banana. Mild fruity yeast taste Not as well bodied as other wit
Pale orange pour. Small white head. Very little lacing. Malt, Hop aroma. Mild, sweet, drinkable lager, medium carbonation, light bitter finish.
Deep mahogany pour. Thick brown head. Toast, fig, caramel nose. Complex malt, toffee plum flavour. Nice warmth. Slightly bitter finish.
Dark browny red pour with small tan head. Caramel & Malt on the nose. Strong toffee and caramel on the tongue. Hoppy warm alcohol finish.
Light gold pour. Small white head. Little lacing. Fine carbonation. Straw fruity aroma. Delicate tropical fruit flavour. Easy drinking.

Light copper pour. Small white head. Low carbonation. Sweet toffee, Banana on the nose. Sweet molasses, toffee and Banana on the tongue.
I find the Banana taste way too synthetic for my liking.
Light gold pour. Creamy white head. Hop, grain & mild fruit aroma. Caramel, buiscuit and crisp malt on the tongue. Medium dry finish.
Pale gold pour. Thick foamy head. Yeasty, fruity aroma. Orange rind and apple on the tongue. Great spicy hoppiness. Spicy, bitter finish.
Cloudy gold pour. Little head, no lacing. Malt, buiscuity aroma. Sweet on the tongue, caramel, wheat, wholesome beer. Thick mouthfeel.
beer_name: Brewers & Union Beast of the Deep

review_blob: Golden pour. Small white head. Subtle malt aroma. More mild malt on the tongue. Very low bitterness. Easy drinking. Must serve cold.
Gold pour. Thick Creamy head. Medium carbonation, lots of floaters. Aroma is mild yeasty. Mild hop taste. Aftertaste of pink sweets.
Deep mahogany pour. Light brown head. Slight lacing. Bread, malt, fruit & yeasty aroma. Roast plum, dark fruits & candy sugar on the tongue.
Cloudy gold pour. Foamy white head. Lightly carbonated. Yeast, clove & Banana aroma. Taste as above with a hint of vanilla. Good Beer.
Cracker of an IPA. Great floral, citrus hop profile with a good malt backbone to back it up.
Cloudy gold pour. Off white lasting head. Aroma is yeasty, malty & some caramel. Buscuit & sweet fruit on the tongue. Medium bitter Finish.
Clear light gold pour. Malt, grassy aroma. Sweet, hoppy, grassy, mildly floral taste. Good lingering dry bitter finish.
Cloudy gold, thick white head. Spicy yeasty citrus grass aroma. Dry, hoppy & spicy palate with citrus notes. Medium bodied. Dry finish
Clear gold pour. Thick white head. Floral hoppy nose, hints of apple. Fresh & hoppy on the tongue, subtle corriander, light fruitiness.
Clear gold, frothy white head. Sweet malty aroma. Good carbonation. Sweet grain taste but disapoints with a heavy metallic finish.
Dark amber pour. Tan head. Sugary, roasted malt, mocah aroma. Taste follows the nose with faint liquorice undertones.
Gold pour, white head, fine lacing. Spicy Belgian yeast on the nose. Citrus and faint corriander on the tongue. Nice maltiness. Smooth mouth.
Amber pour. Thin white head. Aroma is malty, bread, caramel & light hops. As above on the tongue. Cascade shines through well.
